    "title": "A well earned five stars!",
    "language": "en",
    "originalLanguage": "en",
    "text": "There are five reasons why you might want to give a hotel a  5 star review:\n1. Ambiance: The hotel is perfectly situated opposite Hyde Park and as soon as you walk in there is a wonderful atmosphere of a well run and comfortable hotel with everything you could possibly want or need catered for.\n2. Staff: Everyone from the concierge, to reception to the waitresses serving at table seem really to enjoy being helpful and to deal with any queries you might have, it is service with a smile.\n3. Food: This time we only had breakfast but as far as I go it has to be the best breakfast in town.\n4.  The Room:  Ours was on the 14th floor and the panoramic view of London was simply breathtaking, day and night, the kingsized bed was simply luxurious, fit for a king!\n5. The Management: A well run and happy hotel is always down to the Management and here the hotel clearly excels.\n\nAnd so it is an easily earned  five stars from me!",
