    "title": "Outstanding Hotel",
    "language": "en",
    "originalLanguage": "en",
    "text": "The Royal Lancaster is an elegant and refined hotel.  Its location across the street from Hyde Park is lovely and its staff is outstanding.  The bedrooms are little small by American standards but typical and perhaps larger than most European rooms.  The rooms have a good refrigerator, a heated towel rack, plenty of shelf space in the bathrooms, and a comfortable sofa.  The beds and pillows were very good.\n\nThe hotel really shines in its staff.  There is a huge number of them (the staff to guest ratio must be amazingly good) and they are unfailingly professional, polite, and competent.  The concierges are world class.  Special thanks to Sebastian and Matt.  They are so outstanding they probably have their choice of hotels at which to work.  The front desk staff was excellent and professional.\n\nBreakfast was top-notch.  My wife thought it our best ever, and it is certainly in my top three.  Great selection, beautifully prepared, top-quality ingredients, and delicious.  The breakfast staff, of which there must be a hundred, were gracious, friendly, and very helpful.  Special thanks to Viktoria, Yolanda, Ediri, Ayksa, Carolain, and Hannah for taking care of us so well.\n\nHyde Park is immediately accessible from the hotel and is beautiful and completely safe.  We walked there numerous times.\n\nThe hotel is not perfect.  The major problem is outside traffic noise.  There are motorcycles day and night on Bayswater Rd., Westbourne Terrace, and Lancaster Terrace.  We were on the 14th floor facing west, but I don't think one can escape the noise despite the double-glazed windows.  Medium and deep sleepers should have no trouble, but light sleepers may suffer.  Of course, traffic noise in a city is to be expected and most hotels in the city probably have it.  One does become somewhat accustomed to it eventually.\n\nTaxis are always available in front of the hotel and the porters and bellmen are excellent.\n\nOne cannot go wrong with this hotel.  It’s outstanding and is a great value for a top hotel in London.",
    "username": "Tripman66",
    "connectionToSubject": null,
